         <abstract>
            <p>In this paper the author discusses the policies and procedures related to the use of expert witnesses in tort litigation in general and insurance litigation in particular. He also presents the results of a survey of members of the American Risk and Insurance Association regarding their activity in and attitudes toward expert witness work. He concludes that around 50% of ARIA members engage in this work and that they regard it as providing valuable insights for their classroom teaching.</p>
         </abstract>
